model_response.text: Startups can die from releasing something that is full of bugs, not fixing them fast enough, but making a lot of money at a relatively low price. Many startups worry that their competitors will find out about the issue and try to fix it, which can hurt them. In some cases, founders may also make things that are hard to do for their users, leading to poor user experience and driving away customers.
